 Directory options
\par }\pard\plain \s24 \f2\fs20 
\par \pard \s24 The Oberon-2 compiler generates both symbol- and object-files for every source module. This files are stored in the same directory as the source file for default.
\par \pard \s24 
\par \pard \s24 If you want to collect your symbol- and object-files in a different directory, then declare this directory in the {\i Options/Directories} dialogue.
